---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Pedro Teixeira - Metaduck"
  description="Pedro Teixeira - Software Engineer, Tech Writer, Open-sourcerer, and Entrepreneur"
>
  <section class="text-center py-20 relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
      <img
        src="/images/hero-bg4.jpg"
        alt=""
        class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-40"
      />
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900/80 to-slate-900/90"
      >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative z-10">
      <div class="mb-8">
        <img
          src="/images/avatar.jpg"
          alt="Pedro Teixeira"
          class="w-32 h-32 rounded-full mx-auto object-cover border-4 border-green-500/50"
          style="box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.3);"
        />
      </div>
      <h1
        class="text-5xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-6 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wider"
      >
        <span class="text-orange-400">[</span>PEDRO TEIXEIRA<span
          class="text-orange-400">]</span
        >
      </h1>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 mb-8">
        <p class="text-xl text-green-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto font-mono">
          👾 Software Engineer 🖋 Tech writer ☕️ Open-sourcerer 🎸 Wanna-be
          musician 🍼 Father 🚀 Curious
        </p>
        <div
          class="flex items-center gap-4 text-green-300/70 font-mono text-sm"
        >
          <span>🏠 Working from home</span>
          <span>🇵🇹 Portugal</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="sci-fi-card mb-12">
      <div class="p-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-8 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wide"
        >
          BIOGRAPHY
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-8 text-green-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            👶 When Pedro was 10, his father brought home a ZX-Spectrum
            computer. After he plugged it to the power and TV, Pedro typed and
            stared at the blinking cursor. Since then, computers have been an
            important part of his life.
          </p>
          <p>
            👦 At 18 he went to Lisbon to study Software Engineering at I.S.T.,
            and before he finished it he had already started working for the
            software industry.
          </p>
          <p>
            🛠 The first years he spent in consulting for many different
            industries (retail, B2B, telecoms, finance and tourism). During that
            time he specialized in distributed systems and the networking
            protocols that were emerging from this thing called "the internet".
            Always devoted to open-source (he is the author and contributor of
            some famous open-source projects and packages), he has also been the
            writer of 10 books around the subject of Node.js and systems
            architecture.
          </p>
          <p>
            🎟 In 2012 he and some friends founded and helped organize the
            Lisbon JavaScript (LxJS) conferences in Lisbon for 3 years in a row.
          </p>
          <p>
            ⏰ Meanwhile he has joined startups, founded some companies, did
            consulting work and provided training for some big projects in the
            U.K. (Thomas Cook, The Economist, King Fisher, British Gas and
            others).
          </p>
          <p>
            🧪 For some years he also worked on decentralized computing and
            storage.
          </p>
          <p>
            👀 You can still (and hopefully for many years to come) spot him in
            the wild being a technical team leader or a consultant with a taste
            for systems architecture, always interested in developing
            performant, local-first, highly-available and (sometimes)
            decentralised digital information systems.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sci-fi-card mb-12">
      <div class="p-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-8 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wide"
        >
          PUBLICATIONS
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              White paper: Merkle-CRDTs (co-author)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              Latest research on CRDTs and Merkle trees
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://hector.link/presentations/merkle-crdts/merkle-crdts.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm"
            >
              🌍 View PDF
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              Node Patterns Books (2016)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              A collection of short books about Node.js and how it can be used
              to implement several software architectural patterns.
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://leanpub.com/b/nodepatterns"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm"
            >
              🌍 View on Leanpub
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              Professional Node.js - Building Javascript based Scalable Software
              - Wrox
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              Comprehensive guide to building scalable applications with Node.js
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://www.wiley.com/en-gb/Professional+Node+js%3A+Building+Javascript+Based+Scalable+Software-p-9781118240564"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm"
            >
              🌍 View on Wiley
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              Hands-on Node.js (2012)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              Practical guide to Node.js development
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://leanpub.com/hands-on-nodejs"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm"
            >
              🌍 View on Leanpub
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sci-fi-card">
      <div class="p-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-8 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wide"
        >
          CONNECT
        </h2>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 justify-center items-center"
        >
          <a
            href="https://github.com/pgte"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 flex items-center gap-3 font-['Orbitron'] text-sm tracking-wide transition-colors"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
            GITHUB
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://metaduck.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 flex items-center gap-3 font-['Orbitron'] text-sm tracking-wide transition-colors"
          >
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path
                d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm-1 17.93c-3.94-.49-7-3.85-7-7.93 0-.62.08-1.21.21-1.79L9 15v1c0 1.1.9 2 2 2v1.93zm6.9-2.54c-.26-.81-1-1.39-1.9-1.39h-1v-3c0-.55-.45-1-1-1H8v-2h2c.55 0 1-.45 1-1V7h2c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2v-.41c2.93 1.19 5 4.06 5 7.41 0 2.08-.8 3.97-2.1 5.39z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            WEBSITE
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://x.com/pgte"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 flex items-center gap-3 font-['Orbitron'] text-sm tracking-wide transition-colors"
          >
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path
                d="M18.244 2.25h3.308l-7.227 8.26 8.502 11.24H16.17l-5.214-6.817L4.99 21.75H1.68l7.73-8.835L1.254 2.25H8.08l4.713 6.231zm-1.161 17.52h1.833L7.084 4.126H5.117z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            X (TWITTER)
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
